<div class="mb-6">
  <%= link_to "← Back to Items", items_path, class: "inline-block bg-primary text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-dark transition-all duration-200 shadow-md text-lg font-semibold text-content" %>
</div>

<div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-12 max-w-4xl">
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <div class="text-center">

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-content" data-font-size="24">How to Browse & Rent Items</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 text-content" data-font-size="16">Step-by-step instructions for Teachers and TAs on browsing, renting, and listing items.</p>
  </div>

 <!-- Browsing Items -->
<section class="mt-12">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary text-content" data-font-size="18">🔍 Browsing Available Items</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">
    Use the <span class="font-medium">Search Bar</span> on the Items Page to find items. Apply filters to refine your search.
    As an Admin, you are able to also add new items directly into the database.
  </p>
  <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md">
    <p class="text-gray-700 text-content" data-font-size="16">📌 Tip: Click an item to view its details and availability.</p>
  </div>

<!-- Screenshot -->
<div class="mt-6 text-center">
  <div class="inline-block border-2 border-black rounded-md overflow-hidden">
    <%= image_tag "additems.png", alt: "Search and Add New Item Example", class: "max-w-full h-auto" %>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 italic text-content" data-font-size="16">
    Form to add new items on the 'View Items' Page
  </p>
</div>


</section>

  <!-- Renting Items -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary text-content" data-font-size="18">🛒 Renting an Item (Teachers & TAs Only)</h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 mt-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary">
      <p class="font-semibold text-content" data-font-size="16">✅ Eligible Renters:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 text-content" data-font-size="16">
        <li>Teachers</li>
        <li>Teaching Assistants (TAs)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="font-semibold mt-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">❌ Not Eligible:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-content" data-font-size="16">Students must have a TA or Admin rent items on their behalf.</p>

    </div>

    <!-- Screenshot -->
<div class="mt-6 text-center">
  <div class="inline-block border-2 border-black rounded-md overflow-hidden">
    <%= image_tag "rentitems.png", alt: "Search and Add New Item Example", class: "max-w-full h-auto" %>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 italic text-content" data-font-size="16">
    Form to rent items on the 'View Renting' Page
  </p>
</div>

    <div class="mt-6">

      <p class="text-gray-700 font-medium text-content" data-font-size="16">To rent an item, follow these steps:</p>
      <ul class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 mt-2 space-y-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">
        <li>Enter the required details requested.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Create Rental"</strong> on your selected item. Make sure to check the 'Single-use' box if Item can only be used once.</li>
        <li>You will see the details of the rental in the table on the 'View Rentings' Page.</li>

      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- Renting Items -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary text-content" data-font-size="18">🔄 Returning Items</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">
    The status should say rented in red in the Rentings Table. If any issues arise, report them promptly. For damaged items, use the <strong>Comment</strong> button to note the issue on the renting record.

    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="mt-6 text-center">
  <div class="inline-block border-2 border-black rounded-md overflow-hidden">
    <%= image_tag "rentp1.png", alt: "Search and Add New Item Example", class: "max-w-full h-auto" %>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 italic text-content" data-font-size="16">
    You can see that it states the item is rented. 
  </p>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">
    Once the item is returned, you simply click the Rented button. This allows you to mark it as returned and automatically provides a date of the return. 
    </p>
</div>

<div class="mt-6 text-center">
  <div class="inline-block border-2 border-black rounded-md overflow-hidden">
    <%= image_tag "rentp2.png", alt: "Search and Add New Item Example", class: "max-w-full h-auto" %>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 italic text-content" data-font-size="16">
    Status is changed to Returned and Date of the return is provided. 
  </p>
</div>




 

    <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md">

      <p class="text-gray-700 text-content" data-font-size="16">
        📩 All rental records are accessible in the Rentings Table, which is viewable only by TAs and Admins.

      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- Rules & Policies -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary text-content" data-font-size="18">⚠️ Rules & Policies</h2>
    <ul class="text-gray-700 mt-2 list-disc list-inside text-content" data-font-size="16">
      <li>Only Teachers and TAs can rent or list items.</li>
      <li>All damages must be reported immediately.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary text-content" data-font-size="18">💬 Need Help?</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 text-content" data-font-size="16">
      For support, please <a href="mailto:james.reyes@tamu.edu" class="text-primary font-medium">contact James Reyes</a>.

    </p>
  </section>
</div>
